/account/{id}/tax_document/{file_id}.description: This is a longer description for the section that instructions the user on what to do. You can add much more text here.
/account/{id}/tax_document/{file_id}.summary: This is the name of the section

/apply/account_application.description:
The Account Application is used to make the final submission when applying to open a new account.

 Each Account Application that you create requires the inclusion of the IDs of the relevant Account Product, Business Application, Person Application(s), and Deposit objects.

post.description: To create an application for a new bank account, create an Account Application object.This example demonstrates the creation of a Personal account. Business accounts are very similar, but will utilize a few different fields. Please see [https://developers.treasuryprime.com/guides/open-accounts](https://developers.treasuryprime.com/guides/open-accounts) for more information.

account_number_reservation_id.description: ID of the [Account Reservation](https://developers.treasuryprime.com/docs/account-application#account-number-reservations0) object for creating the account with a previously-allocated account number. Can be created with /account_number_reservation.Example: `anr_123`

account_product_id.description: ID of the [Account Product](https://developers.treasuryprime.com/docs/account-product) being applied for, can be retrieved from /account_product.Example: `apt_11ha1payax7042`

bankdata.description: Optional arbitrary data, for the bank's use.

business_application_id.description: ID of the [Business Application](https://developers.treasuryprime.com/guides/open-accounts#2-create-a-business-application) object for the business applying for the account can be created with /apply/business_application.Example: `abus_11hb4dzeb572hh`

deposit_id.description: ID of the [Deposit](https://developers.treasuryprime.com/guides/open-accounts#3-create-a-deposit) object that defines the initial funding deposit for the new account. Can be created with /apply/deposit.Example: `adpt_11hb4fexb57yd8`

person_applications.description: Array of Person sub-objects describing persons associated with this account application, including the primary person. Always [] for business accounts. Can be created with /apply/person_application

primary_person_application_id.description: ID of the [Person Application](https://developers.treasuryprime.com/guides/open-accounts#1-create-a-person-application) object representing the primary person applying for the account.Example: `apsn_11hb4cjwb563zt`

200.description: This how different types of response would look like
Returns a list of all existing Account Applications that have been created, or an empty list if none are available.
